# SharpMod

A modernized, standalone fork of the (abandoned) SHARPpy sounding renderer,
targeting Python 3.11+, NumPy 1.24+, and Qt6 via PySide6.

SharpMod is a modernized, standalone fork of the (abandoned) upstream
[SHARPpy](https://github.com/sharppy/SHARPpy) project. See `LICENSE` for
attribution.

## Repository layout

```
.
├── pyproject.toml        # packaging + dependency pins
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
├── sharpmod/             # the package
│   ├── sharptab/         # derived-parameter computation library
│   ├── io/               # decoders (SPC, BUFKIT, PECAN, WRF-ARW, .npz, UWyo)
│   ├── viz/              # Qt6/PySide6 rendering widgets
│   ├── tools/            # point-sounding extractors (UWyo, ERA5, WRF-ARW, HRRR)
│   ├── tests/            # pytest + Hypothesis suites
│   └── resources/
│       ├── fonts/                # bundled TTFs (importlib.resources)
│       └── uwyo_stations.json    # full UWyo station catalogue (offline)
├── examples/             # sample sounding inputs and reference renders
├── attic/                # legacy prototype + reference dev scripts (untracked build history)
└── .kiro/specs/          # design / requirements / task specifications
```

## Installation

Requires Python ≥ 3.11.

```bash
pip install -e ".[render]"     # core library + render transitive deps
pip install -e ".[era5]"       # + optional ERA5 / GRIB extraction tooling
pip install -e ".[wrf]"        # + optional WRF-ARW (wrfout NetCDF) tooling
pip install -e ".[dev]"        # + pytest / Hypothesis test tooling
```

### Rendering (upstream SHARPpy)

The renderer composes the upstream `sharppy` widget stack (and its bundled
`sutils` package) at runtime, applying Qt6/PySide6 compatibility shims. Upstream
`SHARPpy==1.4.0a5` is on PyPI, **but its wheel metadata carries a stale
`numpy==1.15.*` pin** that conflicts with the modern NumPy this fork needs, so it
cannot be a normal dependency. Install it in a separate `--no-deps` step (its
real runtime needs — `python-dateutil`, `requests`, `numpy` — are already
provided by this package):

```bash
pip install -e ".[render]"
pip install --no-deps "SHARPpy==1.4.0a5"
```

After that, rendering works headlessly (the renderer sets the Qt `offscreen`
platform automatically):

```bash
sharpmod-render examples/soundings/hrrr_point_36.68N_95.66W_f018.npz out.png
```

> Data-source extraction (UWyo, ERA5, WRF) does **not** require the SHARPpy
> render stack — only the `--render` step does.

### Console entry points

`pip install` exposes these commands:

| Command | Module | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `sharpmod-render` | `sharpmod.render` | render a sounding file to PNG |
| `uwyo-sounding` | `sharpmod.tools.uwyo_sounding` | list/search/fetch UWyo soundings |
| `era5-extract` | `sharpmod.tools.era5_extract` | ERA5 point sounding → `.npz` |
| `wrf-extract` | `sharpmod.tools.wrf_extract` | WRF-ARW point sounding → `.npz` |

## Data sources

All three extractors below write the fork's `.npz` point-sounding format and
open through the same renderer path as the HRRR `.npz` sidecar. Add
`--render [out.png]` to any extractor CLI to open the sounding in the app.

### University of Wyoming (observed soundings)

Every fixed UWyo upper-air station is bundled in
`resources/uwyo_stations.json` (built by `sharpmod.tools.build_uwyo_catalog`
from the modern `/wsgi/` server), so stations are choosable offline. The
decoder fetches from the modern `/wsgi/sounding` endpoint and converts the new
server's m/s wind speeds to knots.

```bash
# List / search the full catalogue
python -m sharpmod.tools.uwyo_sounding list --grep norman
python -m sharpmod.tools.uwyo_sounding search 72357

# Fetch an observed sounding and open it in the app
python -m sharpmod.tools.uwyo_sounding fetch 72357 "2024-05-20 00" \
    --out oun.npz --render oun.png
```

```python
from sharpmod.io.uwyo_decoder import UWyo_Decoder
dec = UWyo_Decoder(full_catalog=True)      # resolve against all UWyo stations
UWyo_Decoder.search_stations("denver")     # -> catalogue records
prof = dec.fetch("72357", when_utc)         # -> Profile
```

### ERA5 reanalysis (point sounding)

```bash
python -m sharpmod.tools.era5_extract "2024-05-20 00:00" 35.18 -97.44 \
    era5.npz --render
```

### WRF-ARW model output (`wrfout` NetCDF)

Extracts the nearest grid-point column from a raw WRF run (pressure, height,
temperature, dewpoint, and earth-relative winds), destaggering the vertical
and wind grids and rotating winds via `COSALPHA`/`SINALPHA`.

```bash
python -m sharpmod.tools.wrf_extract wrfout_d01_2024-05-20_00:00:00 \
    35.18 -97.44 wrf.npz --time "2024-05-20 00:00" --render
```

## Fonts

Bundled fonts (JetBrains Mono, Space Grotesk) are resolved package-relative
through `sharpmod.resources`:

```python
from sharpmod.resources import font_path, fonts_dir, font_names

font_names()                       # -> ['JetBrainsMono-Bold.ttf', ...]
font_path("SpaceGrotesk-Regular.ttf")  # -> filesystem Path
fonts_dir()                        # -> directory suitable for QT_QPA_FONTDIR
```
